# Framework-default output-format templates (the resolution MIDDLE branch).
#
# This dir is the framework-shipped, READ-ONLY default tier in the templates
# resolution order (vision §10):
#
#   1. team template      aidlc/spaces/<space>/memory/templates/<artifact>.md   (override)
#   2. framework default   <harness>/tools/data/templates/<artifact>.md          (THIS dir)
#   3. else                the generic >=2-H2 floor                              (fallthrough)
#
# The framework ships NINE default template files here (one per
# discovery-scope artifact — assumptions-record through test-plans; the
# intent-statement deliberately ships none). Every other
# artifact still hits the generic floor until a team authors its own template,
# OR a later PR drops a default <artifact>.md here. The resolution order is
# unchanged, and a team template still WINS over any default in this dir.
#
# Distinct from the TEAM override dir (aidlc/spaces/<space>/memory/templates/,
# via memoryTemplatesDir()): that one a team hand-authors and it WINS over this
# default. This one ships with the engine and is never edited by a user.
#
# A resolved template is used WHOLE-DOC (its ## headings become the expected set
# the required-sections sensor verifies, expected ⊆ output) — no section merge.
# Read by aidlc-sensor.ts (dispatcher → --framework-templates-dir) and
# aidlc-sensor-required-sections.ts (the middle branch). The agent reads the same
# resolution order via core/aidlc-common/protocols/stage-protocol.md.
